# devbox session-secrets manifest — materialize vault projects into app .env / config
# files at login (on tmpfs/RAM), wiped at the last logout. Copy to deploy/secrets.map
# (gitignored) and edit. `configure`/`up` installs it onto the box when present.
#
# One mapping per line:
#
#   <vault-project>   <absolute dest path on the box>
#
#   project = the name you `devbox vault load <project>` (stored at secret/<project>).
#             Locally the file is ./secrets/<project>.env — flat, or organized into
#             folders with path separators joining as dots: the project
#             kash-cards.deploy.prd may live at ./secrets/kash-cards.deploy.prd.env
#             OR ./secrets/kash-cards/deploy.prd.env. Always use the DOTTED name here.
#             FILE MODE: a non-.env file under ./secrets/ (a .pem, .sql, .xml, …) is a
#             project too — its name KEEPS the extension (./secrets/runegate/server.pem
#             is the project runegate.server.pem) and it materializes byte-for-byte.
#   dest    = where your app reads the file on the box. Parent dirs are auto-created;
#             the file there becomes a symlink into RAM. Must be an absolute path.
#
# The project name and the dest filename are independent — so many apps can each use a
# plain ".env" (the directory disambiguates); you only need a distinct project label.
#
# Example:
#   frontend             /home/eddyg/apps/frontend/.env
#   backend              /home/eddyg/apps/backend/.env
#   worker               /home/eddyg/services/worker/.env
#   ramp-enablement.sql  /home/eddyg/apps/backend/deploy/ramp-enablement.sql
#   runegate.server.pem  /home/eddyg/apps/runegate/certs/server.pem
#
# Notes:
# - The vault must be UNSEALED (from your laptop: `devbox vault unseal`) for materialize
#   to run. If sealed at login, it's skipped with a notice; after unsealing run
#   `systemctl --user restart devbox-secrets` on the box.
# - Cleanup only removes our symlink + the RAM copy — never a real file you placed there,
#   and never your local ./secrets or the vault.
